1 Introduction
This document explains how the document controller will control the physical location of the
documents and how to change it from draft status to live, versioning or live to archive.
1.1 Purpose
This procedure defines the steps that should be followed by the document controller to change the
status of the document.
1.2 Scope
This Policy applies to QMSrs internal operations
1.3 Referenced Documents

2 Documentation Control Policy Guidelines
2.1 Approved CCN
This section explains how to issue, update or withdraw a document after getting the
approval.
2.1.1 Issue a document
This section explains how to issue a new document.
To Issue new document:

 Originator get a temporarily document ID from the document controller
 Originator raises CCN, click here (CCN W.I -Add CCN) to view how to raise
CCN
 Automatic mail will be send to the related personnel to Approve the CCN
 Owner and other approval list will approve the CCN
 Automatic mail will be send to the Document controller (DC) that CCN
approved
 DC will save the document in the shared folder with the right access level for
personnel
 DC will assign a document ID and Version number in the “Document List”
module, click here (DL W.I- Add a Document) to view how to Add document
details
 Document will be released and published
 DC will close the CCN , click here (CCN W.I - Close CCN) to view how to
close CCN
2.1.2 Update a Document
This section explains how to update an existing document
To update existing document:
 Originator raises CCN, click here (CCN W.I -Add CCN) to view how to raise
CCN
 Automatic mail will be send to the related personnel to check the CCN
 Owner and other approval list will approve the CCN
 Automatic mail will be send to the Document controller (DC) that CCN
approved
 Document controller (DC) will save a copy of the old version of the document
in the archive.
 DC save the latest version of the documents in the live location
 DC will change the address of the document and version number of this
document in the Document list module
 Old address of the document versions will stay accessible to track changes
 Document will be released and published
 DC will close the CCN , click here (CCN W.I - Close CCN) to view how to
close CCN
2.1.3 Withdraw a Document
This section explains how to withdraw an existing document
To withdraw an existing document:
 Originator raises CCN, click here (CCN W.I -Add CCN) to view how to raise
CCN
 Automatic mail will be send to the related personnel to check the CCN
 Owner and other approval list will approve the CCN
 Automatic mail will be send to the Document controller (DC) that CCN
approved
 The Document controller (DC) will save a copy of the document in the
“Archive”

 DC will change the address of the document in the Document list module
 DC will change the status of the document to be closed

2.2 Rejected CCN
This section explains how to close rejected CCN.
 Originator raises CCN, click here (CCN W.I -Add CCN) to view how to raise
CCN
 Automatic mail will be send to the related personnel to check the CCN
 Owner or any of the other approval list will Reject the CCN and explain the
reason of rejection
 Automatic mail will be send to the Document controller (DC) that CCN had
been Rejected
 DC will close the CCN , click here (CCN W.I - Close CCN) to view how to
close CCN
